First Lady Melania Trump attended a discussion at the United States Capitol regarding the anniversary signing of the Support Act. The Act focuses on reducing drug abuse and addiction, and aligns with Mrs. Trump's BE BEST initiative. The discussion highlighted the Act's support for drug-dependent mothers and babies with neonatal abstinence syndrome, as well as efforts to reduce opioid use during pregnancy and address childhood issues related to substance abuse. Members of Congress also shared how the Act has impacted their communities in the fight against drug abuse. The conversation emphasized the importance of addressing addiction and mental health issues, and praised bipartisan efforts to pass legislation to combat the crisis. Mrs. Trump expressed her appreciation for the Administration's work and called for continued collaboration between the Administration and Congress to support families affected by the drug crisis.